  "notes": [
    "Store each observed leaderboard team as its own entry.",
    "Use the same archetypeId across slight variations of the same build shell.",
    "Keep gear names aligned with the app's existing weapon, costume, materia, and memoria naming when possible.",
    "teamMemoria is a single shared team-level memoria entry.",
    "Each character stores their own two sub costumes in subCostumes."
  ],
  "materiaNotes": [
    "[Element] Breach materia applies a low-pot debuff for that element and can be important setup, not just filler.",
    "Mana Breach applies low-pot MDEF Down. Breach applies low-pot PDEF Down.",
    "Some teams rely on materia-applied low-pot debuffs so follow-up abilities can amplify them.",
    "Example: Aerith with Abraxas can turn an existing low-pot debuff from materia into a high-pot debuff in one use, while Zack's Festive Jacket-style effect raises debuffs one stage at a time.",
    "Cura and Ruinra may appear only as stat sticks based on materia RNG rather than as intended combat casts.",
    "Element materia such as Watera/Watera Blow or Aerora/Aerora Blow can also provide RNG-based elemental potency and MATK/PATK bonuses.",
    "Blow materia variants are PATK-oriented. Non-Blow elemental materia variants are MATK-oriented."
  ],
